President Trump held a press conference in the Oval Office with Guatemalan Minister Enrique Degenhart to announce the signing of a historic asylum agreement between the two countries. The agreement aims to address issues of asylum fraud and abuse, as well as provide safety for legitimate asylum-seekers. Trump also mentioned the progress made in securing the border with Mexico, thanks to their cooperation in deploying troops. He criticized the Democrats for impeding progress on border security and investigations, and expressed his optimism about future trade agreements with the UK and other countries. He also mentioned the possibility of imposing tariffs on French wine and commented on various other topics, including the Federal Reserve, North Korea, and Apple.